rimentally determined thermal transport\ndata do not support superior thermoelectric features. The transition from\nlong-range magnetic order in \\mss\\ to short-range order and spin fluctuations\nin \\msse\\ is explained using the variation of the Mn-Mn distances in the\ntriangle units that constitutes the saw-tooth lattice upon progressive\nreplacement of sulphur with selenium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 May 2019 06:13:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-06"}
